cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel model for Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks that incorporates Sparse Evolutionary Training (SET) procedure to reduce the number of parameters and improve efficiency. It also evaluates the proposed model on sentiment analysis classification datasets. 

It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the proposed model is evaluated on sentiment analysis classification datasets, which is a natural language processing task. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper proposes an evolutionary strategy to adapt the sparse connectivity to the data. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a new model for LSTM networks that improves efficiency and performance. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as LSTM networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image captioning and video analysis.
